triana.types.clipins

Class SequenceClipIn

  • java.lang.Object
    • triana.types.clipins.SequenceClipIn

  • public class SequenceClipIn
extends java.lang.Object
    A index clip-in specifies the position of an object in a index, and optionally either the total number of objects in that index and when this is the last item in the index.

    As with arrays in Java, the indexes of a sequence clipins start a 0 and finish at (length - 1). If the length is not specified then it is set to -1.
